         <abstract id="aspace_9aeb25e5512a09f4391308295c59b378">The collection comprises primarily postcards, most of a racist propaganda nature; several press photographs; and printed ephemera depicting the Italian wars in Ethiopia, as well as present day Somalia and Eritrea. Included are materials relating to the First Italo-Ethiopian War (1895 to 1896) and the Second Italo-Abyssinian War or the Second Italo-Ethiopian War which lasted from October 1935 to May 1936, with the occupation lasting until 1941. The result was the annexation of Ethiopia into Italian East Africa.</abstract>
         <langmaterial id="aspace_79d33810210727dffa0d5ec447cb42cc">
            <language>The materials are in Italian, French, and Spanish.</language>
         </langmaterial>
         <origination label="creator">
            <corpname identifier="http://id.loc.gov/authorities/names/n83042641"
                      rules="aacr"
                      source="naf">
