      <prefercite id="aspace_46c015e6228b5b1a67666f8867d40d27">
         <head>Preferred Citation</head>
         <p>Postcards and Printed Ephemera Documenting the Italian Occupation of Ethiopia (MS 1898). Manuscripts and Archives, Yale University Library.</p>  
      </prefercite>
      <scopecontent id="aspace_81c5d3d380fb69764218b9bb12aeb787">
         <head>Scope and Contents</head>
         <p>The collection comprises primarily postcards, most of a racist propaganda nature; several press photographs; and printed ephemera depicting the Italian wars in Ethiopia, as well as present day Somalia and Eritrea. Included are materials relating to the First Italo-Ethiopian War (1895 to 1896) and the Second Italo-Abyssinian War or the Second Italo-Ethiopian War which lasted from October 1935 to May 1936, with the occupation lasting until 1941. The result was the annexation of Ethiopia into Italian East Africa.</p>  
      </scopecontent>
      <arrangement id="aspace_9c88bdf76cf3f07214db486d0dc9adc2">
         <head>Arrangement</head>
         <p>Materials are arranged as received from vendor.</p>  
      </arrangement>
